# TODO: Integration smoke test for dispatcher alias via beckman → pump → dispatch route.
#
# What's missing to wire this up:
#   1. The orchestrator pump (run_loop) needs a real asyncio event loop running
#      concurrently with the test. In unit tests we have a single event loop and
#      no background pump processing tasks.
#   2. beckman.enqueue(await_inline=True) registers a Future in _inline_waiters
#      and awaits it. The Future is resolved only when on_task_finished() is called
#      by the pump after executing the task. Without a running pump, the Future
#      never resolves and the test deadlocks.
#
# To wire this correctly:
#   - Start a minimal pump loop via asyncio.create_task(orchestrator.run_loop())
#   - Mock dispatcher.dispatch() to return a fake result
#   - Enqueue a raw_dispatch task via dispatcher.request()
#   - Verify dispatcher.dispatch() was called with the right spec
#   - Cancel the pump loop after verification
#
# Deferred because setting up the pump requires a fully wired orchestrator
# (TelegramInterface, beckman DB, nerd_herd) which is integration-level overhead.
# The unit tests in test_dispatcher_alias_compat.py cover the contract
# (request→enqueue→TaskResult→response) via a mocked beckman.enqueue.
